## Template Selection Matrix

| User Need | Template | Modules to Use |
|-----------|----------|----------------|
| Frontend UI only | Template 1 (Frontend) | common + product module with location |
| Serverless events | Template 2 (Serverless) | common + product module with events |
| Frontend + Backend API | Template 3 (Hybrid) | common (requests + functions) + product module (location) |
| OAuth integration (ONLY if required) | Template 4 (OAuth) | common (requests + functions + oauth) + product module |

**CRITICAL: When to Use OAuth vs API Key**

**Use OAuth ONLY when:**
- ‚úÖ Third-party service REQUIRES OAuth (GitHub, Jira, Salesforce, Google APIs, Slack, etc.)
- ‚úÖ User needs to authorize access to their account on the external service
- ‚úÖ App needs to act on behalf of the user
- ‚úÖ External service doesn't offer API key authentication

**DO NOT use OAuth when:**
- ‚ùå External service accepts API keys, tokens, or webhook URLs (Zapier, most REST APIs)
- ‚ùå User can provide a simple API key or webhook URL
- ‚ùå No user authorization flow is needed

**Example:** "Zapier webhook sync" ‚Üí ‚ùå NO OAuth (use webhook URL in iparams) | "GitHub issue sync" ‚Üí ‚úÖ OAuth required

**Default: Use API key in iparams. Only use OAuth if service explicitly requires it.**

